



Winter Hill [Mass.] 10 August 1775.



The subscribers commend the conduct and undaunted courage of William Lee at the Battle of Bunker Hill. He not only fought well himself but give good advice to the men, to place themselves in right order and to stand their ground well, the said William Lee belonging to Capt. Spauldins company in Colo. Reeds Regiment, and is the first or orderly sergeant of Capt. Spauldings company and as their is a vacancie in the same company by a Lieut[s]. Death, it is desired for the Ensign to take his place, and sergeant Lee to take the Ensigns or second Lieut.1
